title: St. Louis woman found fatally shot in car near her home
text:
St. Louis woman found fatally shot in car near her home From staff reports 1 hr ago ( … ) 
ST. LOUIS • Police have identified a 19-year-old woman found fatally injured in a car near her home Tuesday afternoon. 
Officers dispatched to a reported shooting in the 4000 block of Labadie Avenue found Kenisha Davis injured in a car near her home shortly before 4:30 p.m. She was taken to a hospital, where she was pronounced dead. 
Police say she was sitting in the car with another woman when another car pulled up and someone inside opened fire. 
Authorities had no description of the shooter. The investigation is ongoing. 
The address is south of Fairground Park in the Greater Ville neighborhood.
